p36.text:
A carrier operating public rail passenger transport shall, in addition to the obligations specified in § 35, be obliged to:

- a) operate rail transport according to the timetable and tariff;

- b) mark individual rail vehicles or their sets intended for the transport of persons, with the exception of cableways, with the name of the departure and destination station (stop) and mark rail vehicles accessible to passengers with reduced mobility and orientation with the international symbol of accessibility; in the case of tramways and trolleybuses, also with the line number, names of stops, and vehicle registration number.

p37.text:
(1) The carrier shall transport, for the agreed price, a person who requests transport, and shall accept for transport, for the agreed price, luggage and a consignment submitted for transport, if:

- a) the transport can be carried out by the carrier's employees and with equipment suitable for usual transport needs;

- b) the transport is not hindered by circumstances that the carrier cannot avert and whose removal is not within its power;

- c) the contractual transport conditions and conditions stipulated by a special regulation^7) are met.

(2) The carrier is obliged, upon request of the passenger, to ensure the sale of transport documents also for sections operated by other carriers.

p38.text:
(1) The rail administrative authority shall decide on the restriction of the carrier's rail transport for the absolutely necessary period due to:

- a) public interest in other extraordinary rail transport;

- b) safety of rail transport;

- c) impassability of the railway as a result of a natural disaster, accident, or reconstruction of the railway;

- d) accumulation of transported goods on the railway, caused by the railway operator or another carrier.

(2) An appeal against the decision of the rail administrative authority on the restriction of the carrier's rail transport shall not have suspensive effect.

(3) The carrier is obliged to restrict rail transport based on measures issued by administrative authorities authorized to decide in the field of veterinary, plant protection, hygiene services, waste management, or based on an international treaty by which the Czech Republic is bound and which has been promulgated in the Collection of Laws.

(4) The carrier is bound by the restriction of rail transport. It shall publish the resulting transport restrictions.
